In this article, you’ll learn how to add visualization to a pandas dataframe by using pandas styling and options/settings.
The Pandas documentation itself is pretty comprehensive, but if you’re looking for a slightly friendlier introduction, I think you came to the right place.

You can find the post here: [Style Pandas Dataframe Like a Master](https://towardsdatascience.com/style-pandas-dataframe-like-a-master-6b02bf6468b0)

